<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">The specific epithet is a Latin adjective alluding to the large size of the adults.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Elytral surface smooth, striae complete, impunctate, 4 setiferous punctures on interval 3, shoulders rounded. Profemur glabrous. Abdominal sternum VII with 5+5 setiferous punctures.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="habitus">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Habitus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">
dorsal aspect, as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 49–50" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 49 - 50.. 47 Semiardistomis major sp. n. 50 Semiardistomis rugosus (Putzeys). Dorsal aspect. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/19672" pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
